article.headline: Chattanooga 84, UNC-Greensboro 75
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- Nicchaeus Doaks had 21 points and 13 rebounds to lead Chattanooga past North Carolina-Greensboro 84-75 on Saturday night. The Mocs (14-13, 10-6 Southern Conference) won their third straight game and have won 10 of their last 13 to improve to over .500 after a 1-7 start. The Spartans (4-21, 3-13), who led by seven in the first half, have dropped three in a row and nine of 10. The Mocs pulled ahead 51-43 with 11:54 left. After UNC-Greensboro made it 59-58 with 8:09 remaining, Chattanooga sealed the win at the line. For the game, the Mocs made 32 of 49 free throws on 37 UNC-Greensboro fouls. Stephen McDowell added 20 points and Kevin Goffney had 17 points and 16 rebounds for Chattanooga, which also beat the Spartans 72-54 on Jan. 22 to achieve this season's first conference sweep. Mikko Koivisto led UNC-Greensboro with 28 points.
